abstract: House Republican leaders narrowly avoid partial shutdown of Dept of Homeland Security by passing seven-day funding extension for agency; more than 50 Republicans vote against bill, which was proposed after humiliating setback for Speaker John A Boehner in which House voted against funding extension of three weeks.
lead_paragraph: The agreement was reached after a setback for Speaker John A. Boehner and his team earlier Friday, when the House voted against their original plan to extend funding for the department for three weeks.

headline.main: House Passes One-Week Funding Extension for Homeland Security
headline.print_headline: Congress Pushes Shutdown Back Another Week
